About Me
I am a Software Developer


I bring 3 years of comprehensive IT experience encompassing software and web development, with a focus on backend technologies like Node.js, TypeScript, Java, and Python. Proficient in crafting robust and scalable backend solutions, my expertise extends to web development utilizing a spectrum of technologies including CSS, HTML, JavaScript, and frameworks such as React, Bootstrap, and jQuery. I boast adeptness in database systems like MySQL, Microsoft SQL Server, MariaDB, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, and SQLite, further complemented by a firm grasp of continuous integration and deployment tools like Jenkins, Docker, and Ansible, pivotal in streamlining development processes.


My professional journey includes roles at both Tata Consultancy Services and BlackBerry, where I've honed my skills. At Tata Consultancy Services, I served as a backend developer, actively contributing to a transaction chatbot project hosted on Azure cloud. This versatile chatbot, accessible across platforms such as SharePoint, Microsoft Teams, and Team Center, leveraged LUIS and Natural Language Processing techniques to enhance user interactions. My responsibilities also included integrating the chatbot with MySQL databases, ServiceNow, and MuleSoft, illustrating my adaptability in varied integrations. Additionally, I actively contributed to the growth of a SaaS product, enhancing user experience and system performance.


During my recent role as a Software Developer Intern at BlackBerry, I specialized in SharePoint development, where I customized web parts, features, and solutions to improve user experiences. This encompassed crafting apps, master pages, and custom page layouts. My technical skills extended to OAuth authentication, ensuring secure login experiences, and resolving SharePoint web part bugs. I proficiently used CI/CD tools like Jenkins and GitHub for development and deployment. Furthermore, I designed and implemented display templates for search in SharePoint, optimizing search results presentation. My commitment to unit testing and quality testing validated the reliability and functionality of web applications.


I hold a Master of Applied Computing from the University of Windsor, where I achieved a CGPA of 3.7/4, and a Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering from MVGR College of Engineering in India, graduating with a CGPA of 8.52/10. My commitment to staying at the forefront of technology is reinforced by the AZ-204 Developing Solutions for Microsoft Azure certification. Equipped with this robust background, I'm poised to make meaningful contributions to diverse software and web development projects.
